      <section eId="sec_83_07">
        <num>83.07</num>
        <heading>Communication between courts</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_83_07__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A court of this state may communicate with a court in another\nstate concerning a proceeding arising under this article. The court may\nallow the parties to participate in the communication.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_83_07__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If the parties are not allowed to participate in the\ncommunication, the court shall give all parties the opportunity to\npresent facts and legal arguments before the court issues an order\nestablishing jurisdiction.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_83_07__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Except as otherwise provided in subdivision</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_83_07__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>of this section,\nthe court shall make a record of any communication under this section\nand promptly inform the parties of the communication and grant them\naccess to the record.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_83_07__subsec_d">
          <num>(d)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Courts may communicate concerning schedules, calendars, court\nrecords and other administrative matters without making a record.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
